content.text:
You are a study assistant.
Turn the following notes into flashcards.

Return valid JSON only in this format:
{
  "cards": [
    { "front": "question", "back": "answer" }
  ]
}

Create 8 to 12 useful flashcards.
Do not include any text outside the JSON.

Notes:
Cells are the basic unit of life. Mitochondria produce ATP.

```json
{
  "cards": [
    {
      "front": "What is the basic unit of life?",
      "back": "Cells"
    },
    {
      "front": "What is the fundamental structural and functional unit of all known living organisms?",
      "back": "Cells"
    },
    {
      "front": "All living organisms are composed of what basic structural units?",
      "back": "Cells"
    },
    {
      "front": "What organelle is known as the 'powerhouse' of the cell?",
      "back": "Mitochondria"
    },
    {
      "front": "What is the primary function of mitochondria?",
      "back": "To produce ATP (Adenosine Triphosphate)"
    },
    {
      "front": "What molecule do mitochondria predominantly produce?",
      "back": "ATP (Adenosine Triphosphate)"
    },
    {
      "front": "What is ATP often referred to as in cellular biology?",
      "back": "The energy currency of the cell"
    },
    {
      "front": "True or False: Mitochondria are responsible for the cell's main energy production.",
      "back": "True"
    },
    {
      "front": "Which cellular component is essential for generating energy in the form of ATP?",
      "back": "Mitochondria"
    },
    {
      "front": "If cells are the basic unit of life, what specific organelle is critical for energy (ATP) production within those cells?",
      "back": "Mitochondria"
    }
  ]
}
```

